reviewText: Terrible and useless, the Yale course on negotiation was much better.This course doesn't teach anything.
I was really expecting much more from this, more weeks, more content, more exercises. It's a good basic negotiation course
Not great not terrible. It may be a good introduction into negotiation but there is none in-depth knowledge to be found in this course.

G​reat course. Its short. Its insightful. Its easy to take.

Great course about negotating for women. Though, I feel it was more educationa; then applied. The course could have used some interactive exercises to help us develop negotating skills, or at least confidence skills.

I love Golman Sachs 10,000 Women courses because of their practical approach, detailed insight without necessarily providing so much theory, but a very strong foundation onto which to build really significant impacts.
Simple and straigh to the point. Could benefit from more examples though!

The course was really nice and comprehensive. Something that could have made it a bit more challenging would be to include clips of videos in which different parties engage in a negotiation and then have students analyze their behavior.

Although some of the information were basic (to those that has even a little bit of experience in negotiation), I think that this course is ideal for those who are not confident when it comes to negotiation (like myself) and would like to understand more about themselves as a negotiator further. I'd recommend this course to anyone that would like like to build up on their skills, but now knowing where to start. Plus, it's an extremely speedy course, so it's also perfect for those that don't have a lot of time).

I learnt a whole lot that will help strengthen and improve my negotiation skills. I am now quite equipped, no longer naive, in the world of negotiation. I fully, understand phrases or words such as Outcomes, ZOPA, mindfulness, open offer, leverage e.t.c in their proper context and will apply them, in my future deals.  Thanks

Good one to learn basics of Negotiation.The quizzes and exercises were great discussion points. I do feel the course could include more research , facts and figures on negoitiation when it comes to gender.

This course gave me the knowledge to face these conversations with a wider set of tools.

The C​ourse was good,  with a lot of practical information that can be readily used. The pace was reasonably quick and the material was delivered effectively between reading material and completing the exercises.

​I enjoyed taking this course.  I feel better prepared to face the next negotiation in a more prepared and knowledable matter.   I hope to use the resources provided to construct my BGP.   I am also looking forward to  sharing  this course with my co-workers.

Delivered clear, concise material in an easily-digestible manner.  Great way for a business owner to digest and learn material on their own schedule and enhance their growth in an efficient and cost-effective manner.  Great job, whomever put this together!

I have learnt so much especially identifying my negotiating style. This is so helpful as I will be more aware of my own strengths and weakness. The course then teaches how to become a better negotiator.

Thank you Goldman Sachs for this incredible opportunity. My knowledge of negotiation was very poor, but this course really allowed me to understand better how to approach a negotiation, as well as how to use my skills effectively. The informations provided will be very useful for a future career and will surely enroll in other courses from the 10,000 women series!
